        "Id": "mechdef_conjurer_WVR-IIC-S2",
        "Name": "Conjurer",
        "Details": "The Conjurer, designated the Hellhound by the IS, is a medium to short range fighter. The mech is, for all intents and purposes, a Wolverine IIC however the Clans would not be willing to name a mech after Clan Wolverine, and so it was renamed. As a second line mech, most variants use a standard engine, but do mount an endo-steel chassis for reduced weight. This variant, however, also uses an extra-light engine to save as much weight as possible for weaponry. A very late variant produced for the Wolf Empire, this version mounts a mix of clan-spec and Inner Sphere weaponry. It downgrades the engine to a 250-xl and uses the weight savings to mount a rotary AC/5, MASC, Clan Stream SRM-6 and two Clan medium pulse lasers.<br><br>S-class mechs feature upgrades to their armour, thermal management and defensive systems that substantially improve their survivability on the 31st century battlefield.",
